Flames burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a precise patch of the forest ablaze, then flew in a circle above, observing it for a moment. Bizarrely, as it had slowed down, the strange cries behind it had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't get lifted abruptly by a huge red dragon!"
"It's not that unpleasant, isn't it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi; he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws in Thassalin's back to the point where he had made the Thraki bleed, but apparently, he didn't care. However, Thassalin had realized that he had terrified his new friends and had found a clearing to land in.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELL SOMETHING. I SHOULD HAVE CHECKED."
"You were forced to drag us here with you?" Tenuk shouted as he slid down Thassalin's back and landed on the ground. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our strong and brave fighter! How will he catch up with us?"
"He'll find a way," Nissy replied. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy raised an eyebrow and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course, he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive something like Kayel's little car either, and if he started coming to work in a car, it's only because YOU drove us there. He just has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly burst out laughing and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a bit too long to calm down.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINIATURE BIKE MEANT FOR Temthan children. It was so funny! I WISHED I HAD TELEPATHY. That's a precious thought! One I can't share!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's true. But what did you pick up and why did you take off so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took off, and disappeared briefly before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a rare golden and white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. As Yisini demands. The creatures are close."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also froze, their attention drawn to a gap in the clearing. Something big and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this creature opened two massive pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, not bothering with the three smaller creatures in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to get out of the way just in time, but Nyssi was dragged along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nyssi and throwing her onto his back, using his extraordinary long and agile tail, before taking off. The black creature with two wings quickly gave chase.
Kayel blew out a breath as he drew the gun he had on his back, then opened a pouch containing a ammunition belt. He put it on so he could easily access it, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to transform into something that can fly?" Kayel asked.
"Do you want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? I have an ultra-powerful gun in my hands right now, ready to use. I just need to see it to shoot at it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to give himself some space. With a faint, slightly pained growl, his body transformed, his fur replaced by scales, and his arms turned into wings. He quickly returned to his normal blue Thraki form, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Having regained a more normal appearance of a Thraki, Tenuk now had his back covered in scales, but a pair of protruding points had also grown on it, useful for Kayel to grab onto. Tenuk needed a little time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel realized quickly that they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk managed to narrowly avoid it.
I suppose that's the other big frightening monster that was bothering Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow as he tried to shoot at the second beast, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature in pursuit. Kayel awkwardly turned around himself to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was a blessing for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the upper wings of the creature, which screamed in pain and disappeared again under the trees. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it wouldn't certainly be able to catch up.
Further away, Nyssi was desperately clinging on, while Thassalin flew in circles, firing blasts of flames at the dark creature. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight back, and the fireballs didn't seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin stood up, Nyssi took advantage of the opportunity to draw his gun, a reliable rifle. It wasn't of course intended for this type of situation, but a burst of shots would surely be able to at least deter the black beast, wouldn't it?
